Session summary — 2026-04-20

Built tools/edit_planning.py — a local web UI tool for reviewing and editing plan_video.py output before cutting. Single self-contained file (Flask backend + embedded HTML/CSS/JS). Added flask to requirements.txt.

Features:

Side-by-side debug video player + proportional segment timeline (blue = face, amber = body, red = low confidence)
Two-way video sync — clicking a segment seeks the video; active segment highlights as video plays
Editable fields: start_s, end_s, label, subject_focus, description, pan_plan
Adjacent segment cascade — adjusting end_s of segment N automatically updates start_s of segment N+1 (and vice versa), keeping no gaps or overlaps
duration_s auto-recalculates client-side on every edit
Explicit save (Ctrl+S or button), dirty indicator, atomic write to both JSON and sibling CSV
Workflow for Magic_V2B:

python3 tools/plan_video.py footage/magic_clips/Magic_V2B_Yellow_Charlie.mov
python3 tools/edit_planning.py --json .tmp/planning/.../scenes_planning.json --video .tmp/planning/.../debug_planning.mp4
python3 tools/cut_clips.py --planning-csv .tmp/planning/.../scenes_planning.csv footage/magic_clips/magic_clips.csv


